The term '''summa''' is the [[Latin]] word for ''sum''. It is also used as the name for the [[Integral symbol|∫]] symbol used to represent the [[integral]] in [[calculus]]. It was first used to represent the limiting sum ([[Riemann sum]]) that inspired the integral by [[Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz|Leibniz]] on October 29, 1675.
